Bellisario\">Donald P. Bellisario</a>&nbsp;et&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Don_McGill\">Don McGill</a>&nbsp;sont co-créateurs et producteurs exécutifs du premier membre de la&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS_(franchise)\">franchise&nbsp;<em>NCIS</em></a>&nbsp;.&nbsp;En 2020&nbsp;, il s\'agit de la&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_longest-running_scripted_U.S._primetime_television_series\">deuxième plus longue série télévisée américaine non animée et scénarisée actuellement diffusée aux heures de grande écoute</a>&nbsp;, surpassée uniquement par&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Law_%26_Order:_Special_Victims_Unit\">Law &amp; Order: Special Victims Unit</a></em>&nbsp;(1999-présent), et est la 7e plus ancienne scénarisée aux États-Unis. série télévisée aux heures de grande écoute.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>La série avait à l\'origine le titre en partie redondant&nbsp;<em><strong>Navy NCIS: Naval Criminal Investigative Service</strong></em>&nbsp;;&nbsp;cela a ensuite été abrégé en&nbsp;<em><strong>NCIS: Naval Criminal Investigative Service</strong></em>&nbsp;, puis en&nbsp;<em>NCIS</em>&nbsp;.&nbsp;Dans la saison six, un&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS_(season_6)#ep135\">épisode en deux parties a</a>&nbsp;conduit à une série dérivée,&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS:_Los_Angeles\">NCIS: Los Angeles</a></em>&nbsp;.&nbsp;Un&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS_(season_11)#ep252\">épisode en deux parties au</a>&nbsp;cours de la onzième saison a conduit à une deuxième série dérivée,&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS:_New_Orleans\">NCIS: New Orleans</a></em>&nbsp;.&nbsp;Bien qu\'initialement lente dans les notes, battant à peine le Top 30 au cours des deux premières saisons, la troisième saison a montré des progrès, se classant systématiquement dans le top 20, et à sa sixième saison, elle est devenue un top cinq, y étant restée depuis.&nbsp;En 2011,&nbsp;<em>NCIS</em>a été élue émission de télévision préférée des États-Unis dans un&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Harris_Insights_%26_Analytics\">sondage Harris en</a>&nbsp;ligne&nbsp;.&nbsp;La série a terminé sa dixième saison en tant que série télévisée la plus regardée aux États-Unis au cours de la&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2012%E2%80%9313_United_States_network_television_schedule\">saison de télévision du réseau 2012-2013</a>&nbsp;.&nbsp;<em>NCIS a</em>&nbsp;été renouvelé pour une dix-septième saison le 11 avril 2019, dont la première a eu lieu le 24 septembre 2019. Le 3 mai 2020, CBS a renouvelé la série pour une dix-huitième saison,&nbsp;<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS_(TV_series)#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;qui a été créée le 17 novembre 2020.&nbsp;<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/NCIS_(TV_series)#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'NCIS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '143-revision-v1', '', '', '2021-01-08 14:33:59', '2021-01-08 13:33:59', '', 143, 'http://localhost/Paper-Blog/2021/01/08/143-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(158, 1, '2021-01-08 16:28:38', '2021-01-08 15:28:38', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":159,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"http://localhost/Paper-Blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/Six-Feet-Under-Life-Lessons-BTG-Lifestyle-1024x576.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-159\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em><strong>Six Feet Under</strong></em>&nbsp;is an American&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drama\">drama</a>&nbsp;television series created and produced by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alan_Ball_(screenwriter)\">Alan Ball</a>. It premiered on the premium network&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HBO\">HBO</a>&nbsp;in the United States on June 3, 2001, and ended on August 21, 2005, spanning&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_Six_Feet_Under_episodes\">63 episodes across five seasons</a>. It depicts the lives of the Fisher family, who run a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Funeral_home\">funeral home</a>&nbsp;in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Los_Angeles\">Los Angeles</a>, along with their friends and lovers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ensemble_cast\">ensemble</a>&nbsp;drama stars&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peter_Krause\">Peter Krause</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_C._Hall\">Michael C. Hall</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frances_Conroy\">Frances Conroy</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lauren_Ambrose\">Lauren Ambrose</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Freddy_Rodriguez_(actor)\">Freddy Rodriguez</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathew_St._Patrick\">Mathew St. Patrick</a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rachel_Griffiths\">Rachel Griffiths</a>&nbsp;as the central characters. It was produced by Actual Size Films and The Greenblatt/Janollari Studio, and was shot on location in Los Angeles and in Hollywood studios.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><em>Six Feet Under</em>&nbsp;received widespread critical acclaim, particularly for its writing and acting, and consistently drew high ratings for the HBO network. It is regarded as one of the greatest television series of all time, included on best-of lists by&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Time_(magazine)\">Time</a></em>,<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Feet_Under_(TV_series)#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup>&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Guardian\">The Guardian</a></em>,<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Feet_Under_(TV_series)#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<em><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Empire_(film_magazine)\">Empire</a></em>.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Feet_Under_(TV_series)#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup>&nbsp;The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Everyone%27s_Waiting\">show\'s finale</a>&nbsp;has also been described as one of the greatest television series finales.<sup><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Six_Feet_Under_(TV_series)#cite_note-4\">[4]</a></sup>&nbsp;The series won numerous awards, including nine&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emmy_Award\">Emmy Awards</a>, three&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Screen_Actors_Guild_Awards\">Screen Actors Guild Awards</a>, three&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_Globe_Award\">Golden Globe Awards</a>, and a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peabody_Award\">Peabody Award</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '6 feet under', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '6-feet-under', '', '', '2021-01-11 10:44:14', '2021-01-11 09:44:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/Paper-Blog/?post_type=seriestv&#038;p=158', 0, 'seriestv', '', 0),
